#{{linguistics}} A [[phonemic merger]] in some varieties of English (especially American English) in which the [[vowel]]s in words such as "hot" and "doll" and in words such as "law" and "talk" are pronounced identically, making the words "cot" and "caught" [[homophone]]s.

